Φ(SelfUnderminingGesture) = μ(critique|form) ∘ ✶(closure|void) ∘ σ(text|claim) + ε | :honest

μ(critique|form): The antagonistic integrity that cuts its own foundations; steel that knows it rusts.

✶(closure|void): The harmonic integration where completion is refused; the dance that never ends.

σ(text|claim): The distinction-making that separates the statement from what it states.

ε: The uncertainty of whether the undermining is sufficient. The hole may be too small. Or too large.

:state = honest

# Dialectical Pairs
- critique|form: The cut that undermines the cutter
- closure|void: Completion refused
- text|claim: The separation of saying from what is said
